		<h4>Hierarchy and Key Content</h4>
		<p>My next step was to determine what content truly needed to be on the mobile site.  Instead of looking at our main site and weeding out, slowly by slowly, what was less crucial to a mobile user, I began ground-up, with a blank slate, listing out must-haves for launch and nice-to-haves for future releases. (I can definitely appreciate the Mobile First school of thought.)  I discussed and refined this list with the larger group.</p>

		<p>It became clear that the two main content buckets of our site would be:</p>
		<ul>
			<li>Products: learning about product features with a path to purchase.</li>
			<li>Support: getting support for a product a user owns.</li>
		</ul>
		<p>Based on these two buckets, I mapped out a preliminary site hierarchy (which would evolve over time).</p>
