		<h4>High Fidelity Wireframes & Prototypes</h4>
		<p>Once marketing signed off on the look and feel of the site, I began applying the visual language to all the screens.  It's important to note that during this process, UX did evolve, but because of the good chunk of time devoted to signing off on basic UX, the evolution was minimal.</p>
		<p>With these high-fidelity wireframes and design specs, our engineer had what he needed to finish building out the site.  A ton of time was spent ensuring behavior was consistent across mobile devices (thanks to the plentiful Android device sizes and resolutions out there).</p>
		<p>And as usual, I was still involved, clarifying behavior and providing feedback to perfect pixels, most of which showcased my anal-retentiveness around button sizes, font sizes and weights, padding etc. <a href="http://i0.kym-cdn.com/photos/images/small/000/103/740/Me%20Gusta.png?1318992465">Perfect pixels</a>...</p>
