		<h4>Usability Testing & Launch</h4>
		<p>Prior to launch, our qualitative researcher on our Customer Experience team managed to squeeze in a few rounds of usability testing.  In addition to identifying bugs across device types, he prompted users to accomplish several realistic tasks, e.g. "Let's say you're trying to figure out the difference between a Jawbone ERA and an ICON HD.  What would you do?" and "How would you figure out what style of the ERA you wanted?"</p>
		<p>Users were able to complete most tasks with little difficulty, which validated the UI/UX of our site. Bugs were fed back to engineers, and I continued to try and simplify UI where possible.</p>
		<p>Our site launched at the beginning of March.  The new design is currently delivering content to our customers who are seeking product information and support while they're on the go.</p>
		<p>Post-launch, I'm still involved, helping identify bugs, keeping an eye out for any usability improvements, and creating content of new mobile content and pages.</p>
